examples.en: He felt lonely and miserable after his divorce.
They had all miserably famished with hunger.
All of their attempts have flopped miserably.
I failed miserably in my duty to protect her.
I bit my lip miserably and nodded.
The attempt to rescue the hostages failed miserably.
I've had a miserable cold for the past week.
Millions of people have tried to quit smoking and failed miserably (=been completely unsuccessful).
He lived in a miserable little shack.
